en-the-row-re-ups-at-1-billion/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%28=
12%2F26%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&u=
tm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42ab=
d12a ) from the Wertheimers and others this past year. The Row could only g=
row to a certain point in the U.S. before it had to move a meaningful amoun=
t of its operations to Paris. As I=E2=80=99ve always said, brands and opera=
tors should not
focus on replicating something that already exists=E2=80=94in fashion, and =
most other businesses, that strategy almost never works. Also, LVMH has cha=
nged, too. Arnault=E2=80=99s mission is no longer about resurrecting dead b=
rands, but rather restructuring existing ones.

